# 📺 Netflix Titles Dashboard in Tableau

This Tableau project provides interactive visual insights into the Netflix content library. It is built on a dataset of movies and TV shows available on Netflix and showcases trends related to content type, genres, release years, and more.

## 📌 Project Title

**Netflix Titles Analysis using Tableau**

## 📁 File

- `YTP4(Netflix).twbx`: Tableau Packaged Workbook containing all the dashboards and visual analyses.

## 📊 Key Dashboards & Insights

- **Year-wise Content Release**: Visualizes how Netflix’s content library has evolved over the years.
- **Movie vs TV Show Distribution**: Understand the split between movies and TV shows on Netflix.
- **Genre Distribution**: Identifies top genres like Drama, Comedy, and Documentary.
- **Country-wise Content**: Shows where Netflix is sourcing the majority of its content from.
- **Rating Analysis**: Highlights the diversity of content based on audience ratings (PG, R, TV-MA, etc.).

## 📚 Dataset

Data Source: [Netflix Titles Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shivamb/netflix-shows)

The dataset contains:
- Title
- Type (Movie/TV Show)
- Director
- Cast
- Country
- Date Added
- Release Year
- Rating
- Duration
- Genre (Listed In)

## 🔧 Tools Used

- **Tableau Public**
- Data Source: CSV from Kaggle

## 🚀 How to Use

1. Download `YTP4(Netflix).twbx`.
2. Open the file in Tableau Public Desktop.
3. Explore each dashboard interactively to gain insights into Netflix’s content trends.

## 🎯 Objectives

- Identify Netflix's content growth over time.
- Analyze the distribution of content types and genres.
- Explore content diversity by country and ratings.
